00:47:22,539 --> 00:47:24,841
 <i> She brought her a new doll.</i>

507
00:47:24,908 --> 00:47:26,909
<i> I found it underneath her bed</i>
         <i> torn apart.</i>

508
00:47:26,977 --> 00:47:30,246
    <i> I'm talking violently.</i>

509
00:47:30,314 --> 00:47:32,181
            -<i> Wow.</i>
  - I know it's just a doll,

510
00:47:32,249 --> 00:47:34,617
  but I can't help but think
it might better if it were gone.

511
00:48:08,852 --> 00:48:10,820
      I'll be right back.

512
00:48:30,107 --> 00:48:31,440
             Lily?

513
00:48:42,085 --> 00:48:43,386
             Lily?

514
00:49:03,874 --> 00:49:05,041
         Where's Lily?

515
00:49:05,108 --> 00:49:06,542
Oh, God, honey, you scared me.

516
00:49:06,610 --> 00:49:08,077
        Where is she?!

517
00:49:09,746 --> 00:49:11,414
            Claire!

518
00:49:13,383 --> 00:49:14,583
         Where is she?

519
00:49:14,651 --> 00:49:16,919
        Come on, honey.
    Claire, it is too late.

520
00:49:16,987 --> 00:49:18,587
       Put it-- Claire!

521
00:49:20,490 --> 00:49:21,791
           - Claire!
        - Where's Lily?

522
00:49:21,858 --> 00:49:23,793
          - Stop it!
- How could you do that to her?

523
00:49:23,860 --> 00:49:26,662
      She was my friend!
        My only friend!

524
00:49:26,730 --> 00:49:28,864
           Stop it!

525
00:49:28,932 --> 00:49:32,268
  She did not belong to you!
 She belonged to someone else.

526
00:49:32,336 --> 00:49:36,205
             - Ow.
